            "updated_at": "2014-07-14T14:43:15Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "FYI, you can call `app.add_template_global(whatever[, 'somename'])` to register global vars, functions, etc. for your templates. And if you want to do it directly on a function, use the corresponding decorator:\n\n```\n@app.template_global('whatever')\ndef foo():\n    pass\n```\n\nThe name is optional, it defaults to the function's name.\n"
